3 Tomatoes (about 1 lb)
1 T olive oil
¼ c onion chopped
1 clove garlic chopped
1 t Fresh thyme 
½ T butter

Remove core and stem from tomatoes.  Blanch in boiling water for 10-15 seconds.  Peel.  Halve each across their equator.  Squeeze to remove seeds, straining out to retain the juice.  Roughly chop tomatoes.  

Sauté the oil and onions for 1-2 minutes, the add garlic, sauté another minute, then add thyme, sauté another minute, then add strained juice, bring to a boil for 1-2 minutes.  Add tomatoes, a dash of salt, dash of sugar, dash of black pepper, and bring to a boil.  Continue cooking 3-4 minutes.  Finish with the butter.  

Jacque Pepin 
